dismissalText.commentary: Ryan Watson run out (de Villiers) 31 (50b 4x4 0x6 82m) SR: 62

dismissalComment.html: good-length ball outside the off, Brown pushes to cover and sets off for a single. The fielder is AB de Villers. He gets to the ball early, lines up the stumps and has a go. Bang on target and Ryan Watson, who is running to the danger end, knows there is no chance of him making it back in time. The decision is referred to the third umpire, but there is no real need. Watson is on his way ...

headshotImage.caption: Andrew Hall player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Andrew Hall player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Andrew Hall gets the breakthrough. Majid Haq falls to a fatal poke outside off stump. Full in length, angling away, Haq opens the bat-face, tries to run it down to third man and nicks it behind. Scotland lose their first wicket.
Hamilton is gone. After pottering around for some time, he suddenly decides to have a go - drives on the up, but sends it straight to cover.
Super catch by Kemp. Full-pitched outside off stump and Blain slices it away over cover . Kemp runs in and dives low to his left to take a stunner.

headshotImage.caption: Charl Langeveldt player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Watts falls after a stiff resistance. He looks pretty shattered. Has an uncharacteristic flash at a length-delivery outside off, gets an edge and is swallowed at first slip.
Maybe he should not have gotten off the mark. That single gave him too much confidence. He charges down the track and yorks himself.

commentTextItems.html: Out of the ground! Kemp finishes things off in style. Waltzes down the track and biffs a fullish delivery over long-on. Over the few spectators, over the roof and onto the street.

commentPostTextItems.html: South Africa win by 7 wickets. Another minnow bashing from them. Smith looted a 65-ball 91, de Villiers pinched a fifty and Prince got some time in the middle. Good day's work for SA.
This is Sriram Veera, signing off. Adios.
